[{"category":"section","location":"#Tartaros","page":"Home","text":"Documentation for Tartaros.\n\n","title":"Tartaros"},{"category":"type","location":"#Tartaros.AbstractGHFCorrection","page":"Home","text":"()\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tartaros.AbstractGHFCorrection"},{"category":"type","location":"#Tartaros.GHFDataset","page":"Home","text":"GHFDataset{Tx, Ty, Tg}\n\nA geothermal heat flux dataset on a regular grid.\n\nFields\n\nx: first-axis coordinates (e.g. longitude or projected easting), length nx\ny: second-axis coordinates (e.g. latitude or projected northing), length ny\nghf: GHF values of size (nx, ny), in units\nunits: physical unit string (default \"mW m⁻²\")\nsource: dataset name or citation\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tartaros.GHFDataset"},{"category":"type","location":"#Tartaros.NoGHFCorrection","page":"Home","text":"()\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tartaros.NoGHFCorrection"},{"category":"type","location":"#Tartaros.TopographicGHFCorrection","page":"Home","text":"()\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tartaros.TopographicGHFCorrection"},{"category":"method","location":"#Tartaros.correct!-Tuple{AbstractMatrix, Any, Any, AbstractGHFCorrection}","page":"Home","text":"(\n\ncorrect!(\n    ghf::AbstractMatrix,\n    z_bed,\n    z_bed_mean,\n    correction::AbstractGHFCorrection\n)\n\n\n)\n\nSame as correct, but modifies ghf in-place.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tartaros.correct!"},{"category":"method","location":"#Tartaros.correct-Tuple{Any, Any, Any, AbstractGHFCorrection}","page":"Home","text":"(\n\ncorrect(\n    ghf,\n    z_bed,\n    z_bed_mean,\n    correction::AbstractGHFCorrection\n) -> Any\n\n\n)\n\nReturn the corrected GHF value (or field) given bed elevation z_bed and its spatially-averaged counterpart z_bed_mean.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tartaros.correct"},{"category":"method","location":"#Tartaros.interpolate_ghf-Tuple{GHFDataset, AbstractArray, AbstractArray}","page":"Home","text":"interpolate_ghf(dataset, x_target, y_target) -> Array\n\nBilinearly interpolate dataset.ghf onto (x_target, y_target). Returns NaN for target points outside the dataset extent.\n\nx_target and y_target must use the same coordinate system as dataset.x and dataset.y. They may be arrays of any shape; the output matches that shape.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tartaros.interpolate_ghf"},{"category":"method","location":"#Tartaros.load_ghf-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"Home","text":"load_ghf(filepath; x_name, y_name, ghf_name, units, source) -> GHFDataset\n\nRead a GHF NetCDF file and return a GHFDataset.\n\nKeyword arguments\n\nKeyword Default Notes\nx_name \"x\" Variable name for the x-axis\ny_name \"y\" Variable name for the y-axis\nghf_name \"ghf\" Variable name for the GHF field\nunits \"mW m⁻²\" Physical unit label (metadata)\nsource \"\" Dataset citation (metadata)\n\nCommon dataset variable names\n\nLucazeau (2019): x_name=\"lon\", y_name=\"lat\", ghf_name=\"heat_flow\"\nMartos et al. (2017, 2018): x_name=\"lon\", y_name=\"lat\", ghf_name=\"Q\"\nShapiro & Ritzwoller (2004): x_name=\"lon\", y_name=\"lat\", ghf_name=\"ghf\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tartaros.load_ghf"},{"category":"method","location":"#Tartaros.smooth-Tuple{AbstractMatrix, Real, Real, AbstractSmoothingKernel}","page":"Home","text":"smooth(z, dx, dy, kernel)\nsmooth(z, dx, kernel)\n\nSpatially smooth the field z on a regular grid with spacing dx × dy using kernel. Boundary cells are extended by nearest-neighbor repetition. Returns a Matrix{Float64} of the same size as z.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Tartaros.smooth"}]
